    92                              <1> .try_next_port:
    93                              <1>     ; Not HID on current port. Scan remaining ports on same controller
    94                              <1>     ; before giving up and calling xhci_init for the next controller.
    95                              <1>     ; This handles the case where a boot USB drive is on port 0 and
    96                              <1>     ; the mouse is on a subsequent port of the same xHCI controller.
